conbody.p: Create an arc from a combination of options including the start point, second point, end point, center, included angle, direction, and length of chord.

section.title: Methods to create an arc
section.p: There are three methods to begin creating an arc:
You can press the Ctrl key while drawing an arc to change its direction from counterclockwise to clockwise.

dlentry.dd: Begin creating an arc by specifying a start point then:
Specify a point along the arcs circumference.
Specify the end point of the arc.
Begin creating an arc by specifying a center point then:
Specify the start point of the arc.
Specify the end point of the arc.
Begin creating an arc from the last drawn arc or line segment, following its angle, then:
Specify the end point of the arc. The arc is drawn tangent to the previous segment.

section.title: Additional options within the ARC command
section.p: After you begin creating an arc, the following options may be available:

dlentry.dd: Specify the included angle of the arc.
Specify the direction of the arc.
Specify the radius of the arc.
